25-year-old Tope Dunsin was on Thursday docked by an Osun State Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ile-Ife for theft during church vigil. He however, pleaded not guilty to the two-count charge of entering with ulterior motives and stealing slammed on him. The police prosecutor, Inspector Emmanuel Abdullahi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Nov 16, 2019 around 3:50 am at the Redeemed Christian Church of God, Moremi, Iloro, Ile-Ife. Abdullahi said that the defendant entered church during the vigil and stole a hand bag, Nokia 215 handset, OAUTHC I.D. card and a bunch of house key. He added that the defendant also stole one Holy Bible and cash sum of N53, 000, total sum of #63,000, property of one Ajayi Adebimpe. The Defence Counsel, Mr Bonaventure Olatoye, applied for the bail of the defendant in most liberal term and promised that his client would not jump bail, but would stand his case. Magistrate Muhibah Olatunji granted the bail of the defendant in the sum of N200,000 with two sureties in like sum among other bail conditions as she adjourned until March 16, for hearing of the case. 